From b5e00af6224a77beeca081a6399a1af2e6296c72 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: claude <claude@anthropic>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 19:28:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] feat(card): add TRL + completion as sibling metric to
 readiness

Adds a Technology Readiness Level (TRL) block to the readiness card,
anchored to the SERB / ANRF MAHA MedTech Mission framework.

This is the same vocabulary BIRAC, MAHA MedTech evaluators, and IKP
use when assessing medtech funding applications, so it makes the card
directly speak the language of grant bodies and incubators.

Architecture:
- TRL is a SIBLING metric to readiness, not a composite. Three numbers
  stay independent on the card: Readiness /10 (paperwork), TRL 1-9
  (technical/clinical maturity), Risk H/M/L (patient/regulatory).
  This preserves the 'Readiness != Risk' engineering rule.
- Two tracks: investigational (full 9 levels) and has_predicate (TRL
  6/7 collapse into MD-3/MD-7 application). Track picked from
  classification.novel_or_predicate.
- Each level is anchored to a CDSCO form/license, so TRL claims are
  objectively verifiable rather than vibes-based.
- Completion % is non-linear (TRL 3 = 22%, TRL 7 = 78%, TRL 9 = 100%)
  to reflect that later stages cost materially more time and money.

Implementation:
- lib/engine/trl.ts: framework definitions + deriveTRL() fallback
- lib/schemas/readiness-card.ts: TRL block (optional, additive)
- components/card/TRLBlock.tsx: visual rendering
- components/card/ReadinessCard.tsx: layout slot below badges
- app/c/[share_token]/page.tsx: backfill TRL for legacy cards
- lib/engine/synthesizer-system-prompt.ts: rubric so future runs
  populate TRL natively
- scripts/verify-trl.ts: 4/4 calibration archetypes pass

No breaking changes: existing cards backfill TRL via deriveTRL(),
schema field is optional, BadgeRow + ReadinessCircle untouched.
